roofs.name: L1 Bandwidth (single-threaded)
roofs.desc: L1 cache roof represents the maximum bandwidth of L1 cache for your current hardware. Measured with optimized sequence of SIMD load and store operations iterating over the array that fits entirely into L1 cache.

roofs.desc: L2 cache roof represents the maximum bandwidth of L2 cache for your current hardware. Measured with optimized sequence of Intel SSE/AVX/AVX-512 load operations iterating over the array that fits entirely into L2 cache but does not fit into L1.

roofs.name: SP Vector Add Peak (single-threaded)
roofs.desc: Single-precision vector ADD roof represents the maximum number of floating-point operations per second (FLOPS) for your current hardware when using unrolled loop of vector ADD instructions.

roofs.name: DP Vector Add Peak (single-threaded)
roofs.desc: Double-precision vector ADD roof represents the maximum number of floating-point operations per second (FLOPS) for your current hardware when using unrolled loop of vector ADD instructions.

roofs.name: L1 Bandwidth
roofs.desc: L1 cache roof represents the maximum bandwidth of L1 cache for your current hardware. Measured with optimized sequence of SIMD load and store operations iterating over the array that fits entirely into L1 cache.

roofs.name: L2 Bandwidth
roofs.desc: L2 cache roof represents the maximum bandwidth of L2 cache for your current hardware. Measured with optimized sequence of Intel SSE/AVX/AVX-512 load operations iterating over the array that fits entirely into L2 cache but does not fit into L1.

roofs.name: L3 Bandwidth
roofs.desc: L3 cache roof represents the maximum bandwidth of L3 cache for your current hardware. Measured with optimized sequence of Intel SSE/AVX/AVX-512 load operations iterating over the array that fits entirely into L3 cache but does not fit into L2.

roofs.name: DRAM Bandwidth
roofs.desc: DRAM roof represents the maximum bandwidth of DRAM memory on your current hardware. Measured with optimized sequence of Intel SSE/AVX/AVX-512 load operations iterating over the array that does not fit in CPU caches.

children.caption: INT+FLOAT Arithmetic Intensity
children.tooltip: INT+FLOAT AI is a measure of INT+FLOAT Giga OPs performed by program relative to the amount of Gigabytes required to those operations.

children.caption: FP Arithmetic Intensity
children.tooltip: FP AI is a measure of GFLOPs performed by program relative to the amount of Gigabytes required to those operations.

children.caption: INT Arithmetic Intensity
children.tooltip: INT AI is a measure of GINTOPs performed by program relative to the amount of Gigabytes required to those operations.

functionsAndLoops.caption: Time in 3 Vectorized Loops
functionsAndLoops.warning: Time spent in vectorized loops is noticeably less than in scalar loops. Suggestion: introduce more vector parallelism using OpenMP* or other vectorization methods - explore the Performance Issues and Why no Vectorization columns in the Survey report.
